â¡ï¸A status code in Node.js (or any web server) is a 3-digit number that tells the client (browser, Postman, etc.) about the result of a request.

**ğŸ¤”How Status Codes Work in Node.js**

â¡ï¸When the server processes a request, it sends a response with a status code.
â¡ï¸The status code tells the client whether the request was successful, failed, or needs action.

#Common HTTP Status Codes in Node.js
##Success Codes (2xx) â†’ Request was successful.

â¡ï¸200 OK â†’ Everything is fine!
â¡ï¸201 Created â†’ A new resource was created (used for POST requests).

##Redirection Codes (3xx) â†’ Request needs to be redirected.

â¡ï¸301 Moved Permanently â†’ URL has changed.
